At some point we renamed  'Optimise Indexing' to 'Clean Journal Entries' in 'Admin > Scheduled Jobs'. The [docs|https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/DOC/Scheduled+Jobs] still reference the old data, and seem to have an old screenshot too.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This bug report is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding bug report|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-36761].
  {panel}

I am trying to implement this new plug in for our company 

https://marketplace.atlassian.com/plugins/fr.spectrumgroupe.confluence.plugins.glossary

The features only appear to work when using the Global Look and Feel theme (not Documentation).  Aside for installing the plug in, is there special requirements for implementing this plug in?

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-36758].
  {panel}

When we preview a PDF file in fullscreen mode and we press "Page up/down" it does not go to the next page. This only scroll up/down the page. We'd like to have an option to go to next/previous page and we can use this feature in our meeting in presentations.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-36756].
  {panel}

Users with ‘Create’ or ‘Edit’ permissions should actually see inline comments. Thus they should be visible only to users who can edit pages, not to anonymous users. 

This would be a big improvement, because the inline comments feature is particularly great for small groups of collaborators during the content drafting phase. Please see my blogpost [https://blog.k15t.com/2015/02/confluence-5.7%3A-inline-comments-vs.-page-comments] for more thoughts on this topic.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This bug report is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding bug report|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-36754].
  {panel}

In Space Operations > Export > XML Export, this text is displayed:

{code}
Full Export (includes pages not visible to you)
Generates a XML file for each page in this space, including those not visible to you, and excluding blogs, comments, and attachments.
{code}

Contrary to what the text says, the resulting zipfile does include comments and attachments. This makes sense because it's a full export, but the text is confusing.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-36750].
