It would be handy to embed a Confluence search directly in another website, instead of just adding a link. The search results would send the user over to Confluence (if it allows anonymous access, or the user is logged in).

*Example use case:* in the company website, embed a "Search our documentation" widget that would direct the user to a knowledge base in Confluence.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-36664].
