As per [CONF-21139], you do not intend on exposing child pages on the "Restricted Pages" tab. Can you at least indicate that this page has child pages that are being hidden? As an OnDemand (and therefore not a true) administrator, it's quite confusing to find that there's a page you can't see or find in any way.

My Use Case:
I was trying to copy a page into a space, but the first attempt appeared to time out. After copying, I got an error message saying that there was already a page with that name in the space, but direct browsing, searching, and looking in 'Restricted Pages' resulted in nothing. I ended up needing to enter a support request as I thought the timed out copy attempt had created a ghost page I couldn't access. In the end, it turned out that another manager had created a page with the name I was trying to use, however as it was a child page I had no way of knowing where this page was or even that it was an actual page.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-36650].
  {panel}

While testing inline comments, I noticed that clicking the x or hitting ] does close the in line comment window.  Typing ] again does not reopen the window.  this is inconsistent with [ toggling the view of the left menu pane on and off.

I realize this may be seen as a feature request since the help shows that ] is for "Close inline comment".  But, to me, this is inconsistent behavior.  And, short of adding a new inline comment, I haven't found out how to get the inline comment dialogue back.

