When we receive mail notifications of our confluence, the output is rather ugly. To be more precise, the mail contains the name of the macros, its parameters and some content. Especially, if many macros are used the notification itself will get unclear / confusing.

For a more human readable view, it would be very nice if these mails are rendered as HTML (just like viewing a page) instead of displaying parameters. This would be a great improvement of usability!

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
