From each Confluence major version (5.x, 4.x, 3.x) we have different appearances for Confluence, mostly related to CSS/HTML in use. Sometime, companies could need to keep the same appearance after upgrading Confluence due to the company information or other requests. 

This is an improvement request to give the system-administrator permissions to change the default look of Confluence to the same used in order versions. For example, if you are in Confluence 5.x, in the Look&Feel session you would have an option to select the one from older versions to keep the same appearance.

